description:
Continued from the pages of Cable & Deadpool. Soldier. Hero. X-Man. Nathan Summers, the former mercenary known as Cable, is many things to many people, but above all he is a mutant. Born with special abilities that distinguish him from normal humans, he has fought to prevent his dwindling race's extinction. Now charged with protecting the first mutant born with M-Day, the day when all but one percent of mutantkind lost their powers, he has escaped with the " messiah baby" into the timestream. Abandoning his world and his allies, Cable knows that wherever he lands he'll have to fight for survival.

Although a comic named Deadpool & Cable issue 26 is technically just a one-shot, it follows the lines and the numbering of this Cable series.

description:
Terry Moore's follow up to the impressive Strangers in Paradise series has a tall order to live up to. Echo is the story of two women. One alive and hunted the other dead and in need of avenging. Its a radical change of story from the Stranger's series but anyone who knows SIP will know that radical turns is what Moore can pull off. This takes place in the Strangers universe and there are minor character crossovers and plenty of intrigue and mysticism combine with Moore's distinctive artwork making this a series to watch.

description:
BLOODPOOL: Mini

Once new recruits for the Youngblood program the Bloodpool participants were poked, prodded, drugged and operated on in order to ensure their future as field agents in Youngblood. Unfortunately this was not to happen. After the events of "Extreme Sacrifice" the funding for the program was canceled (just not before the participants had been irreversibly altered) and it's members sent packing.
On their way out of the compound, secretly given permission by Youngblood field leader Shaft, the Bloodpool participants liberate some weapons and ordinance classified "outdated" and headed off. The participants broke into two groups and the primary members of the program literally ran head first into a kidnapping at gunpoint.
Operating on instinct alone the Bloodpool participants leaped from the vehicle, saved the intended victims and took the check written to them on the spot as an omen regarding their future: super powered mercenaries.
name: Bloodpool
